    <Label name="lblWarning" id="e765ee8a-4a2f-4fe9-909f-f1ad2dd1df08">
        <caption>When the Save option is selected and the Finish button clicked, then the cells on the 'Source data worksheet' are cleared and the workbook is saved and stored in the system. Excel will be automatically closed and any temporary files and directories will be cleaned up. If you select Discard and click the Finish button, then Excel is closed without saving the changes in the system. Anytemprary files and directories are cleaned up.</caption>
